Reference-contexts: Although neural network computing has been the method of choice for classification using this type of data [2,3], it is usually difficult to make a biochemical interpretation of the classification scheme. The use of Genetic Programming (GP) has been reported as part of a consensus diagnosis approach <ref> [5] </ref> and was particularly interesting as it made different errors in the classification as compared to a neural network. GP has been used in classification of non-medical data [6,7]. The task is to classify tumours from 1 H NMR spectra which give information about biochemical compounds in a tissue.
