Reference-contexts: Scores were calculated for each sample from these 20 Varimax vectors and used as inputs for the GP classification. GP used class labels as outputs with two possible classes (meningioma = -1; non-meningioma = +1). The GP program used was in Lisp following Koza <ref> [7] </ref>. The terminal set consisted of the 20 Varimax scores, labelled A-S and U (T being a reserved word in Lisp). The functions used were taken from those shown in Table 1. The selection used method was fitness-proportionate and the generation method ramped half and half.
